�@This course introduces students to mass communication research. It contextualizes research 
programmes within the cultural, theoretical and methodological concerns of their times.
�@The module also introduces students, through workshop activity, to basic research skills and 
methodologies required in the undertaking of research in mass communication. 
These include a variety of qualitative and quantitative methods coupled with an address to the 
need to use, and to distinguish between, primary and secondary research data.
 

